)  [static]
 

Get a string that describes this language-type.

The string returned is short or full, eg swedish will return "swe" or "swedish".

Parameters:
langType The language type to return a string for.
fullName Default false. If the name of the language should be the full name.

LangTypes::language_t LangTypes::getStringAsLanguage (  const char *  langType,
bool  fullName = false
)  [static]
 

Get the language described with a string ignoring case, eg "swe" or "SWE" (only mc2, otherwise it is case sensitive ).

If fullName is true, the full name will be matched instead. The language as string should always be in English.

Parameters:
langType The string.
fullName Use e.g. "swedish" instead of "swe"
Returns:
The language type, if no match invalidLanguage is returned.
